text: A larger splash particle containing an arrangement of pixels resembling a loaf has been added.
Added textures from the Standard Galactic Alphabet, used for enchanting libraries.
Added a texture used by angered villagers.
Added a positive green effect, then used for villagers.
Added textures used for firework trails.
Added a flash circle particle effect for firework explosions.
Added "glitter" particles then used for end rods and shulker bullets.
Added the dark heart texture for damage infliction.
Added the particle for sweep attacks.
Added particles for bubbles at the top of bubble columns popping.
Added a diverse array of conduit particles.
Conduits now only use one particle. All the other conduit particles were removed.
The sweep texture has been changed to have shading and dark pixels.
All of the campfire smoke particles have been rotated 90 degrees counterclockwise, with the exception of the last two, which have instead been moved a pixel up and to the left.
With the splitting of particles.png, the original two splash particles, which became unused over time, have now been removed.
The sweep particles, which have also been split now, are 32x32 in size rather then their previous 32x16.
The crit particle has been changed as to no longer be asymmetric.[1]
Added the vibration particle, the first to use a looping animation.
